The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Funds in place for Bina plant

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 27: A consortium of 20 lenders, comprising domestic banks and financial institutions, have committed a 14-year project finance term loan aggregating to Rs 6,387 crore to Bharat Oman Refinery Ltd (BORL). 

 BORL is a 6-million-tonne greenfield refinery being set up by Bharat Petroleum Corporation Ltd at Bina in Madhya Pradesh.

 Apart from the refinery, associated infrastructure, including crude receiving facilities at Vadinar in Gujarat, a 935-km cross-country pipeline and a 126-mw captive power plant, also forms part of the project.

 This transaction is the countrys largest syndicated project finance deal. The sole financial adviser and arranger was SBI Capital Markets Ltd (SBICap), the investment bank from the SBI group. 




